05010nam a22005775i 9780674290099DE-B159720220830111616.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220830t20222022mau    fo  d z      eng d  a97806742900997 a10.4159/97806742900992doi  a(DE-B1597)634166  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  amaucUS-MA 7aHIS0320002bisacsh1 aMogilner, Marina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut12aA Race for the Future :bScientific Visions of Modern Russian Jewishness /cMarina Mogilner. 1aCambridge, MA : bHarvard University Press, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (352 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tIntroduction: Jews, Race, and the Challenge of (Post)Imperial Modernity -- tI. THE SCIENCE OF RACE -- t1. The Dawn of the Jewish Race in the Late Nineteenth-Century Russian Empire -- t2. Samuel Abramovich Weissenberg: “Provincializing Europe” through Jewish Racial Self-Description -- t3. Arkadii Danilovich El’kind: Constructing a Jewish “Cultured Nation” -- t4. Lev Iakovlevich Shternberg: The Political Science of Jewish Race -- tII. THE BIOPOLITICS OF RACE -- tA Necessary Introduction: Jewish Biopolitics as a Victim of Aphasia -- t5. Russian Jewish Physicians and the Politics of Jewish Biological Normalization -- t6. Medical Statistics and National Eugenics -- t7. Civil War and the Biopolitics of Survival -- t8. The Gray Zone of Jewish Biopolitics and Its Place in Soviet Modernity -- tConclusion: At the Finish Line -- tAbbreviations -- tNotes -- tAcknowledgments -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe forgotten story of a surprising anti-imperial, nationalist project at the turn of the twentieth century: a grassroots movement of Russian Jews to racialize themselves.In the rapidly nationalizing Russian Empire of the late nineteenth century, Russian Jews grew increasingly concerned about their future. Jews spoke different languages and practiced different traditions. They had complex identities and no territorial homeland. Their inability to easily conform to new standards of nationality meant a future of inevitable assimilation or second-class minority citizenship. The solution proposed by Russian Jewish intellectuals was to ground Jewish nationhood in a structure deeper than culture or territory—biology.Marina Mogilner examines three leading Russian Jewish race scientists— Samuel Weissenberg, Alexander El’kind, and Lev Shternberg—and the movement they inspired. Through networks of race scientists and political activists, Jewish medical societies, and imperial organizations like the Society for the Protection of the Health of the Jewish Population, they aimed to produce “authentic” knowledge about the Jewish body, which would motivate an empowering sense of racially grounded identity and guide national biopolitics. Activists vigorously debated eugenic and medical practices, Jews’ status as Semites, Europeans, and moderns, and whether the Jews of the Caucasus and Central Asia were inferior. The national science, and the biopolitics it generated, became a form of anticolonial resistance, and survived into the early Soviet period, influencing population policies in the new state.Comprehensive and meticulously researched, A Race for the Future reminds us of the need to historically contextualize racial ideology and politics and makes clear that we cannot fully grasp the biopolitics of the twentieth century without accounting for the imperial breakdown in which those politics thrived.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311078579140uhttps://do